cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.LO

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata for regular expressions.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper studies the size of the automata.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with combinatorial objects (regular expressions) and their properties.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper studies the worst-case size of the automata.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is less likely but still possible as regular expressions are often used in logic and the paper deals with their automata representation.
